.SH "NAME"
scsi_add_lun \- allocate and fully initialze a scsi_device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ scsi_add_lun('u
.BI "int scsi_add_lun(struct\ scsi_device\ *\ " "sdev" ", unsigned\ char\ *\ " "inq_result" ", int\ *\ " "bflags" ", int\ " "async" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIsdev\fR
.RS 4
holds information to be stored in the new scsi_device
.RE
.PP
\fIinq_result\fR
.RS 4
holds the result of a previous INQUIRY to the LUN
.RE
.PP
\fIbflags\fR
.RS 4
black/white list flag
.RE
.PP
\fIasync\fR
.RS 4
1 if this device is being scanned asynchronously
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Initialize the scsi_device
\fIsdev\fR\&. Optionally set fields based on values in *\fIbflags\fR\&.
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
SCSI_SCAN_NO_RESPONSE: could not allocate or setup a scsi_device SCSI_SCAN_LUN_PRESENT: a new scsi_device was allocated and initialized
